
[1]gastric

   GAS'TRIC, a. [from Gr. the belly or stomach.]

   Belonging to the belly, or rather to the stomach. The gastric juice is
   a thin, pellucid liquor, separated by the capillary exhaling arteries
   of the stomach, which open upon its internal tunic. It is the principal
   agent in digestion.
